The Spanish language analysis in mimic has been done mainly by Sergio Oller. The
phonetic transcriptions are done using Saga, a GPL-3 software from the Research Center on
Language and Speech Technologies and  Applications TALP at the Universitat Politècnica
de Catalunya, in Barcelona.

The Saga software has been written by José B. Mariño and Albino Nogueiras and it is
available under the GPL license at https://github.com/TALP-UPC/saga. Licenses for
commercial privative applications can be obtained by contacting asuncion.moreno@upc.edu.


